<item>
            <title>[JCR-1598] Problematic exception handling in Jackrabbit WebApp</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1598</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>In this project, the cause of the exception is often ignored, and only the message of the cause is used, as in:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
} catch (Exception e) {&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;log.error(&amp;quot;Error in configuration: {}&amp;quot;, e.toString());&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;throw new ServletException(&amp;quot;Error in configuration: &amp;quot; + e.toString());&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
An additional problem is that when using ServletException(String message, Throwable rootCause), the rootCause is not used in printStackTrace(), that means the cause is not logged. See also: &lt;a href=&quot;http://closingbraces.net/2007/11/27/servletexceptionrootcause/&quot;&gt;http://closingbraces.net/2007/11/27/servletexceptionrootcause/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
It is therefore better to convert &lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;throw new ServletException(&amp;quot;Unable to create RMI repository. jcr-rmi.jar might be missing.&amp;quot;, e);&lt;br/&gt;
to&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;ServletException s = new ServletException(&amp;quot;Unable to create RMI repository. jcr-rmi.jar might be missing.&amp;quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;s.initCause(e);&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;throw s;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
